    "title": "Immediate Requirement Medical Officer at Roche India Advisory Limited",
    "description": "Roche India Advisory Limited has an exciting opening for a Medical Officer at our Lucknow office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Roche India Advisory Limited:\nRoche India Advisory Limited is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Any graduate with relevant experience\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Flexible working hours\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Lucknow, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Roche India Advisory Limited!",
